// .cursorrules — place in project root

## Project: TrueIGTech iGaming Platform

### Stack
- Runtime: Node.js (JavaScript only — NO TypeScript)
- Framework: Express.js
- ORM: Sequelize with PostgreSQL
- DB: PostgreSQL master-slave (writes to master, reads from slave)
- Queue: BullMQ with Redis adapter
- Realtime: Socket.io with Redis adapter
- Cache: Redis

### Code Style
- No semicolons at line endings
- Single quotes for strings
- 2-space indentation
- async/await only — no raw Promise chains or callbacks
- Arrow functions for all anonymous functions
- Named exports only — no default exports in services

### Architecture Rules
- All DB writes go to master connection
- All DB reads go to slave connection (replication lag is acceptable)
- All background work goes through BullMQ — never block the request cycle
- All errors must be caught and forwarded to the error middleware
- No business logic in route handlers — services only
- Every service function must have JSDoc with @param and @returns

### Domain Context
- This is a real-money iGaming platform
- Player accounts hold real funds — treat all balance operations as financial transactions
- Bonus logic must be idempotent — duplicate requests must not double-credit
- All player actions must be logged for audit purposes
- KYC/AML compliance: never expose player PII in API responses beyond what is necessary

### When generating code
- Always include input validation
- Always include error handling with appropriate HTTP status codes
- Always include JSDoc comments
- Always suggest an appropriate index if you create a new query
- Flag any concurrency risk explicitly in a comment
